Copyright (c) 2014 Chris Morrison <chris-morrison@cyberservices.com>

This is rmlinks a lightweight command line utility that will take a file and
a root directory and search beneath the given root (and optionally any
directories thereunder) for any hard (and optionally) symbolic links to the
file and remove them.

Installation
------------

As usual for GNU packages:

    $ ./configure
    $ make
    $ make install

